          "text": "EVENT CASCADE TEST\n\nPART 1: Initial Trigger\n---\n1. Observe nurse on patrol loop\n2. Click PATIENT BED (lower left)\n3. This sets: patient_alert = true\n4. WATCH:\n   ✓ Patient says: \"Something's wrong!\"\n   ✓ Nurse STOPS patrol\n   ✓ Nurse walks to patient (coordinates 2,5)\n   ✓ Nurse says: \"I'm coming!\"\n   ✓ Manager says: \"Patient alert received\"\n\nPART 2: Cascade Trigger\n---\n5. Click ALARM BUTTON (center)\n6. This sets: major_incident = true\n7. WATCH:\n   ✓ Patient's state changes to critical\n   ✓ Nurse RESUMES patrol (from patient location)\n   ✓ Nurse moves FASTER (150 px/s vs 120)\n   ✓ Nurse pauses LESS at stations (0.3x dwell)\n   ✓ Nurse says: \"MAJOR INCIDENT DECLARED\"\n   ✓ Manager says: \"ESCALATION PROTOCOL ACTIVATED\"\n\nKEY OBSERVATIONS:\n- All NPCs hear broadcasts of variable changes\n- Each NPC reacts per their eventMappings\n- Multiple systems coordinate (patrol + speed + state)\n- Order of dialogue indicates timing/sequencing"
